<s docid="LA042789-0025" num="85" wdcount="17"> She later told an interviewer, "It
was, at least for me, true love from the start" .</s>

<s docid="LA042789-0025" num="86" wdcount="17"> Exchanging vows seven months
later, the pair began what was for the most part a troubled marriage.</s>

<s docid="AP890426-0123" num="12" wdcount="20"> 1951 _ They form Desilu
Productions with $5,000 and ``I Love Lucy'' begins its historic six-year
domination of television comedy.</s>

<s docid="AP890426-0185" num="44" wdcount="42"> As testament to their value as
prime-time stars, Miss Ball and Arnaz signed an $8 million, no-cancellation,
two-year contract with CBS in 1953 _ the largest in television history at
the time and a figure scarcely any TV star can touch today.</s>

<s docid="LA042789-0025" num="110" wdcount="35"> Instead, in the years since the
original 153 "I Love Lucy" episodes were telecast, they have been shown and
reshown in virtually every country around the globe, earning an estimated
$50 million to $100 million.</s>

<s docid="LA042789-0025" num="123" wdcount="34"> "I never wanted to be an
executive, but when my marriage to Desi broke up after 19 years, I couldn't
just walk away from my obligations and say 'forget it,' " Miss Ball
explained.</s>

<s docid="AP890426-0126" num="12" wdcount="19"> Miss Ball died of a ruptured aorta
at Cedars-Sinai Medical Center in Los Angeles Wednesday morning, hospital
officials said.</s>

<s docid="AP890426-0126" num="13" wdcount="3"> She was 77.</s>

<s docid="AP890427-0098" num="11" wdcount="34"> An outpouring of sympathy from
presidents to childhood neighbors followed the death of Lucille Ball, but
many said the queen mother of comedy will live on through television reruns
and her influence on comedy.</s>

<s docid="AP890426-0185" num="26" wdcount="19"> But she also embodied an even
greater treasure _ the gift of love,'' President Bush said in a
